data.chText: 滤器；过滤器
data.enText: a device containing paper, sand, chemicals, etc. that a liquid or gas is passed through in order to remove any materials that are not wanted

data.chText: 空气过滤器；滤油器
data.enText: an air/oil filter

data.chText: 咖啡过滤器；滤水器
data.enText: a coffee/water filter

data.chText: 咖啡机滤纸
data.enText: filter paper for the coffee machine

data.chText: 他吸没有过滤嘴的香烟。
data.enText: He smokes cigarettes without filters.

data.chText: 滤光器；滤声器；滤波器
data.enText: a device that allows only particular types of light or sound to pass through it

data.chText: 筛选（过滤）程序
data.enText: a program that stops certain types of electronic information, email, etc. being sent to a computer

data.chText: （交通红灯指示不得直行的同时，表示可左转或右转的）分流指示灯
data.enText: a light on a set of traffic lights showing that traffic can turn left or right while traffic that wants to go straight ahead must wait

data.chText: 过滤
data.enText: to pass liquid, light, etc. through a special device, especially to remove sth that is not wanted

data.chText: 所有饮用水必须经过过滤。
data.enText: All drinking water must be filtered.

data.chText: 使用能有效滤掉紫外线的防晒霜。
data.enText: Use a sun block that filters UVA effectively.

data.chText: 我的秘书很会替我推掉不相干的电话。
data.enText: My secretary is very good at filtering my calls (= making sure that calls that I do not want do not get through) .

data.chText: （用程序）筛选，过滤
data.enText: to use a special program to check the content of emails or websites before they are sent to your computer

data.chText: 缓行
data.enText: to move slowly in a particular direction

data.chText: 门开了，人们开始徐徐通过。
data.enText: The doors opened and people started filtering through.

data.chText: 慢慢传开；走漏
data.enText: to slowly become known

data.chText: 人们对这场空难的了解一点点多起来。
data.enText: More details about the crash are filtering through.

data.chText: 渗入；透过
data.enText: to come into a place slowly or in small amounts

data.chText: 阳光从窗帘透了进来。
data.enText: Sunlight filtered in through the curtains.

data.chText: 仅可左转行驶
data.enText: to turn left at traffic lights while other vehicles wanting to go straight ahead or turn right must wait
filter sth↔out

data.chText: 过滤掉
data.enText: to remove sth that you do not want from a liquid, light, etc. by using a special device or substance

data.chText: 过滤掉尘粒；滤光；用过滤法除杂质
data.enText: to filter out dust particles/light/impurities

data.chText: （用专门的系统、装置等）过滤掉，筛除，淘汰掉
data.enText: to remove sb/sth that you do not want from a large number of people or things using a special system, device, etc.

data.chText: 这个测验是用来淘汰不适合的求职者。
data.enText: The test is used to filter out candidates who may be unsuitable.

data.chText: 这个软件可筛除含儿童不宜内容的互联网网站。
data.enText: The software filters out Internet sites whose content is not suitable for children.
filter sth↔out

data.enText: to filter out dust particles/light/impurities

data.chText: 这个测验是用来淘汰不适合的求职者。
data.enText: The test is used to filter out candidates who may be unsuitable.

tr: device that removes something from whatever passes through it
an electrical device that alters the frequency spectrum of signals passing through it
remove by passing through a filter
run or flow slowly, as in drops or in an unsteady stream
example: water trickled onto the lawn from the broken hose

value.def: To filter a substance means to pass it through a device which is designed to remove certain particles contained in it.

example.ex: The best prevention for cholera is to boil or filter water, and eat only well-cooked food.
example.tran: 预防霍乱的最佳方法是将水煮沸或过滤，并且只食用煮熟后的食物。

value.def: A filter is a device through which a substance is passed when it is being filtered.
A filter is a device through which sound or light is passed and which blocks or reduces particular sound or light frequencies.

example.ex: You might use a yellow filter to improve the clarity of a hazy horizon.
example.tran: 可以使用黄色滤光器让模糊的视野更加清晰。

value.def: If light or sound filters into a place, it comes in weakly or slowly, either through a partly covered opening, or from a long distance away.

example.ex: Light filtered into my kitchen through the soft, green shade of the cherry tree.
example.tran: 光线透过樱桃树柔和的绿阴隐约照进我的厨房。

value.def: When news or information filters through to people, it gradually reaches them.

example.ex: It took months before the findings began to filter through to the politicians...
example.tran: 调查结果数月后才传到从政者的耳朵里。

example.ex: News of the attack quickly filtered through the college.
example.tran: 有关袭击的消息很快就在该学院中传开了。

example.ex: ...as indications filter in from polling stations.
example.tran: 随着从投票站透露出各种迹象

example.ex: ...the horror stories which were beginning to filter out of Germany.
example.tran: 开始传出德国的恐怖故事

value.def: A traffic filter is a traffic signal or lane which controls the movement of traffic wanting to turn left or right.
To filter out something from a substance or from light means to remove it by passing the substance or light through something acting as a filter.

example.ex: Children should have glasses which filter out UV rays...
example.tran: 儿童应该戴上滤除紫外线的眼镜。

example.ex: Plants and trees filter carbon dioxide out of the air and produce oxygen.
example.tran: 花草树木会过滤掉空气中的二氧化碳并制造氧气。
